'''Uttarakhand Open University''' (Hindi: <U+0909><U+0924><U+094D><U+0924><U+0930><U+093E><U+0916><U+0902><U+0921> <U+092E><U+0941><U+0915><U+094D><U+0924> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0936><U+094D><U+0935><U+0935><U+093F><U+0926><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E><U+0932><U+092F>) is a university located in the city of [[Haldwani]] in the Indian state of [[Uttarakhand]]. This is the only Open University in the state.

The university was established by an Act Of [[Uttarakhand Legislative Assembly]] on 31 October 2005.<ref>Act 23 of 2005 of the Uttarakhand Legislative Assembly</ref> Recognized by [[Distance Education Council]], [[University Grants Commission (India)|University Grants Commission]]<ref>http://uou.ac.in/system/files/ugc_recogni.pdf</ref> and listed in [[Association of Indian Universities|AIU]]<ref>http://www.aiuweb.org/Members/MembersU.asp</ref>

==Programmes 2011/2012==
See http://uou.ac.in/programmes

==Study Centers==
The university operates under the physical boundary of the Indian State [[Uttarakhand]], and has a network of eight Regional Centres and 300+ Study Centres across the state.<ref>University Centers http://uou.ac.in/sc</ref>

==Schools==
* School of Social Science
* School of Management Studies
* School of Tourism and  Hotel Management
* School of Agriculture
* School of Health Sciences
* School of Education
* School of Computer Sciences and Information Technology
* School of Sciences
* School of Languages

==MoU==
The University has signed MoUs with [[Tata Motors]], [[Hiltron Calc]], [[University18]], [[IETS]], [[IKC India]] and various others.

